Package au.csiro.pathling.fhirpath.parser

Class ParserContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.csiro.pathling.fhirpath.parser.ParserContext
  • public class ParserContext
extends Object
    Context and dependencies used in the parsing of a FHIRPath expression. The parser context can change through the parsing of an expression as it passes through different states (e.g. aggregation, inside the arguments to a function). Change to the parser context is only permitted through a limited set of public setter methods.
    Author:
    John Grimes

      • getGroupingColumns

        @Nonnull
public List<Column> getGroupingColumns()
        The context may contain zero or more grouping columns. If the context of evaluation is a single resource, the resource identity column should be the one and only column in this list. Otherwise, columns that provide the relevant groupings should be in here.
